## 5. Success Criteria

### 5.1 User Engagement Metrics

| Metric | Target | Measurement Period |
|--------|--------|-------------------|
| Daily active users (DAU) | 60% of registered users | Monthly |
| Mood check-in completion rate | 75% of users complete 5+ check-ins/week | Weekly |
| Feature utilization | 80% of users engage with 3+ features | Monthly |
| Retention rate | 70% of users remain active after 3 months | Quarterly |

### 5.2 Impact Metrics

| Metric | Target | Measurement Period |
|--------|--------|-------------------|
| Emotional improvement | 65% report reduced distress after 4 weeks | Monthly |
| Crisis intervention success | 90% of users in crisis access helpline/professional support | Ongoing |
| Community engagement | 50% participate in peer support discussions | Monthly |
| Professional help seeking | 40% of users with severe symptoms seek therapy | Quarterly |

### 5.3 Safety Metrics

| Metric | Target | Measurement Period |
|--------|--------|-------------------|
| Crisis response time | <30 seconds to display emergency resources | Real-time |
| Harmful content detection | 99% of harmful content flagged and removed | Daily |
| User safety reports | <1% of users report feeling unsafe or triggered | Monthly |

